<p>Maybe it is something like from a Ray Bradbury story. Kids find these things in regular toy stores (or nowadays online) and parents buy them for them and never notice the weirdness. Shop clerks say &quot;Weird, I never saw that before&quot; and sell it anyway.</p>
<p>With the exception of Little Misters (which are specifically called out as a limited collectors item) Wondertainment things seem to be aimed at competing with normal toys at middle class price points.</p>

